[`raise`](http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man3/raise.3.html) sends the signal to the calling thread.

[`kill`](http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/kill.2.html) sends a signal to the specified process or thread. 

To send the signal to the parent process, instead of 
```
raise(SIGUSR1);
```
do
```
#include &lt;unistd.h&gt;
// ...
kill(getppid(), SIGUSR1);
```

